Please translate each line literally into English and Cornish.

1 Quando si parte il gioco de la zara,
2 colui che perde si riman dolente,
3 repetendo le volte, e tristo impara;

4 con l’altro se ne va tutta la gente;
5 qual va dinanzi, e qual di dietro il prende,
6 e qual dallato li si reca a mente;

7 el non s’arresta, e questo e quello intende;
8 a cui porge la man, più non fa pressa;
9 e così da la calca si difende.

query.result:
**English:**

1 When the game of dice begins,
2 the one who loses remains sorrowful,
3 repeating the throws, and sadly learns;

4 with the other, all the people go;
5 some go in front, and some take him from behind,
6 and some from the side bring him to mind;

7 he does not stop, and he listens to this one and that one;
8 to whom he gives his hand, he no longer hurries;
9 and so he defends himself from the crowd.

**Cornish:**

1 Pythegyll an gwari a'n zara,
2 an hini a golla a wra trist,
3 ow kul ow holya, ha trist ow dyski;

4 gans an aral yth esa oll an dus,
5 nebes a wra kyns, ha nebes a'n kemer a-dhyworth,
6 ha nebes a-dhyghow a'n gorra dhe ves;

7 ha na wra sevel, ha hemma ha henna a glew,
8 dhe neb a ro dhynnergh y dhewl, nyns yw festinyk;
9 ha gwellhevel orth an wonvos yth omdhiskwedh.

